  {
    "title": "Interstellar",
    "year": 2014,
    "type": "Movie",
    "poster": "interstellar.jpg",
    "rating": "⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐",
    "review": "god this movie is so gutting and beautiful. the film itself is very visually stunning and unique, but the story is just absolutely perfect and heartbreaking. i knew nothing about the movie going into it, so just finding out he was the ghost, and how he even told himself to stay is so devastating. the scene where he finds out his children have aged 20 years is just shot and acted perfectly. and the starting video being about cooper but being told by his daughter after the fact, it was all perfection and perfectly put together. i love stories about time, and this one might be my favorite\n\nLast Watched: April 28th, 2026",
    "favorite_movie": false,
    "favorite_show": false,
    "watchlist": false
  },
  {
    "title": "Everything Everywhere All at Once",
    "year": 2022,
    "type": "Movie",
    "poster": "everything-everywhere-all-at-once.jpg",
    "rating": "⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐",
    "review": "this movie is so beautiful and fun. not many movies take advantage of the multiverse concept that aren't superhero films, so to see one be done so well and unique is amazing. its just such a fun idea of doing random things to get to a new multiverse for essentially a stat increase. me personally im jumping to every possible multiverse and leveling myself up, even if i gotta jump on the plug. i love the unique multiverses too, the rock one and the pinata are just a masterclass. and the cat universe of course, i just love unique displays of infinite possibilities. the title cards, music, acting, and visuals are just off the charts. the action scenes are done so well with the slow motion and where the fights go. i absolutely love the message, of both life and generational trauma. life is meaningless, but why does that have to make it a bad thing? if nothing matters, EVERYTHING matters.\n\nLast Watched: March 17th, 2026",
    "favorite_movie": true,
    "favorite_show": false,
    "watchlist": false
  },
  {
    "title": "The Substance",
    "year": 2024,
    "type": "Movie",
    "poster": "the-substance.jpg",
    "rating": "⭐⭐⭐⭐½",
    "review": "i truly and honestly don’t even know what to say. this film isn’t subtle with its messages, but my god does it go to lengths to convey it. the noise, atmosphere, and camera work do a REMARKABLE job making you feel uncomfortable and uneasy all-throughout, and the ending genuinely shocked me and left me baffled. took me entirely off guard. don’t watch while eating or in public though 🙂👍\n\nLast Watched: October 4th, 2025",
    "favorite_movie": false,
    "favorite_show": false,
    "watchlist": false
  },
  {
    "title": "Sinners",
    "year": 2025,
    "type": "Movie",
    "poster": "sinners.jpg",
    "rating": "⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐",
    "review": "was absolutely blown away by the music and cinematography in this film. the story was phenomenal, and it caught me off guard how fast we were thrown into this story and how no punches were pulled. i like the random ensemble that was fighting, i think they blended well and had great chemistry together. i wish to see prequels of the twins past, and the evident sequel sounds exciting. not to mention the wonderful acting on everyone, it goes without saying.\n\nLast Watched: January 27th, 2026",
    "favorite_movie": true,
